-- Ecowas Investment Bank of Togo Sells $59 Million Worth of 2017 Bonds
-- Etonam Akakpo-Ahianyo
-- 2010-07-16T08:11:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/ecowas-investment-bank-of-togo-sells-59-million-worth-of-2017-bonds.html

          
          
             The  Ecowas Bank for Investment and
Development  said it began selling 30 billion CFA francs ($59.2
million) worth of bonds yesterday to fund loans in West Africa.  
 The securities, which mature in 2017, will be on offer
until Aug. 31,  Christian Adovelande , chairman of the lender,
told reporters in the Togolese capital, Lome. The bonds carry a
6.75 percent coupon, he said.  
 The  Economic Community of West African States  has 15
members, including Benin,  Burkina Faso , Cape Verde, Gambia,
Ghana, Guinea,  Guinea-Bissau , Ivory Coast, Liberia, Mali, Niger,
Nigeria, Senegal, Sierra Leone and Togo.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Etonam Akakpo-Ahianyo in Lome via Johannesburg at
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        